  "prompt": "If I buy wireless Bluetooth headphones with a USB charger, will they work like wired headphones if they're plugged into my computer usb via USB cable?",
  "response": "Wireless Bluetooth headphones with a USB charger are primarily designed to work wirelessly via Bluetooth connection. However, some models may also offer the functionality to work as wired headphones when connected via USB.\n\nWhether they will work as wired headphones when plugged into your computer will depend on the specific model and design of the headphones. Here are a few considerations:\n\n1. **USB Audio Support**: Some Bluetooth headphones support digital audio input via USB, meaning they can function as wired headphones when connected to a computer through a USB cable. Check the product specifications or user manual to see if your headphones have this feature.\n\n2. **Charging Only**: For many Bluetooth headphones, the USB connection is only intended for charging the battery and not for audio transmission. If this is the case, plugging them into your computer via USB will not enable wired audio functionality.\n\n3. **Driver Installation**: In some instances, the headphones may require specific drivers or software to enable USB audio functionality. Make sure you have installed any necessary drivers provided by the manufacturer.\n\n4. **Auxiliary Input**: If your headphones also come with an auxiliary (3.5mm) input port, you can use them as wired headphones using a standard aux cable. This is independent of USB capabilities but provides a wired connection option.\n\nTo determine if your specific model supports USB audio functionality, it's best to consult the manufacturer's documentation or customer support.",
